comments: Haliburton (IND) brings his forearm to rest on White's (BOS) side and the contact is marginal.
Turner (IND) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Turner (IND) is drawn into the air towards Brown (BOS), initiating contact that causes him to fall to the floor.
Horford (BOS) firms up over his right leg and marginal contact occurs as Haliburton (IND) attempts to defend around the screen.

Holiday (BOS) initiates contact in the direction Haliburton (IND) is moving.  From all available angles, and given the direction and level of contact, it does not appear that Holiday dislodges Haliburton. This play was also reviewed by the league office for a potential flop by Haliburton, and ultimately deemed embellished but not overtly theatrical.
Turner (IND) raises his right arm up into White's (BOS) arm as he gains control of the rebound, but the contact is marginal.
Haliburton (IND) makes clean contact with the ball during White's (BOS) jump shot attempt and any contact with his hand on the ball is incidental.
Haliburton (IND) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes more than two steps before releasing his jump shot attempt.

Replay review of the foul called on Siakam (IND) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Siakam was called for making contact with Brown's (BOS) wrist during rebounding. Upon review, Brown and Siakam were also observed fouling each other while positioning for the rebound, with Siakam fouling Brown by grabbing his arm and then Brown grabbing Siakam's jersey.  Since Siakam committed the first foul in the sequence, and that foul was deemed proximate to the foul called, Siakam maintained the foul and the challenge is deemed unsuccessful.
Horford (BOS) places a hand on Nembhard (IND) as he returns to the floor during the rebound but he does not dislodge him from his position.
Nembhard (IND) loses control of the ball as he falls to the ground and he legally recovers the ball on the floor before immediately releasing a pass.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Nesmith (IND) is out of bounds while in control of the ball.
Tatum (BOS) has his arms extended as Haliburton (IND) switches onto him and the contact is marginal.
Nesmith (IND) makes clean contact with the ball and any ensuing contact with White's (BOS) arm is marginal.
Turner (IND) makes contact with the ball and incidental contact with Tatum's (BOS) hand on the ball as he elevates into his shooting motion.
Tatum (BOS) commits a take foul on Haliburton (IND).
Brown (BOS) briefly grasps and releases Siakam's (IND) jersey during the throw-in and the contact does not affect Siakam's FOM.
Brown (BOS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Siakam (IND).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Siakam (IND) makes contact with the ball while out of bounds.
Tatum (BOS) firms up over his left leg and does not deliver contact to Nembhard (IND) during the screen.
Siakam (IND) obtains a legal guarding position in front of Brown (BOS) before he enters his shooting motion.  Brown elevates upwards into Siakam's head/face, but the contact is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) maintains a hand on Haliburton's (IND) side, which he removes as Haliburton begins his shooting motion.
Holiday (BOS) establishes himself in Nembhard's (IND) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
White (BOS) makes contact with Haliburton's (IND) arms, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Siakam (IND) briefly grasps and releases Brown's (IND) jersey off ball.
Turner (IND) cleanly dislodges the ball from Brown (BOS) as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Turner (IND) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Tatum (BOS) and Nembhard (IND) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Haliburton (IND) retreats away from Tatum (BOS) during the driving shot attempt.
Turner (IND) moves laterally into White's (BOS) path and initiates contact that occurs prior to the start of White's upward shooting motion.
Tatum (BOS) and Nembhard (IND) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
McConnell (IND) makes illegal contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm as he defends the shot near the rim. The contact occurs after Tatum gathers the ball and continuation is correctly awarded.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Haliburton (IND) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Brown (BOS) cleanly dislodges the ball from Siakam (IND) as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Siakam (IND) reaches in and Brown (BOS) moves through the contact in transition.
Siakam (IND) obtains a defensive possession in front of Tatum (BOS), who runs into him and the ensuing contact is incidental.
McConnell (IND) brings his left hand towards the ball, and the ensuing contact with Holiday's (BOS) arm is marginal.
Haliburton (IND) brings his right hand towards the ball, and the ensuing contact with Holiday (BOS) is marginal.
Haliburton (IND) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Nembhard (IND) brushes White's (BOS) upper body during the shot near the rim.
Horford (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position during Siakam's (IND) drive to the basket and the lower body contact between the two players as they return to the floor is incidental.
Nembhard (IND) and Tatum (BOS) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Haliburton (IND) commits a take foul on Holiday (BOS).
White (BOS) commits a take foul on McConnell (IND).
Horford (BOS) and Siakam (IND) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.

Replay review of the foul called on Tatum (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Tatum and Toppin (IND) engage during the free throw attempt, with Tatum called for wrapping Toppin. Although Toppin also engages with Tatum, there is no clear and conclusive evidence he fouls Tatum first and that the call should be overturned.
Siakam (IND) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
Turner (IND) is firming up over his left leg with his arms slightly forward, and the contact with Holiday (BOS) is marginal.
